def: Of or pertaining to the southeast; southeasterly.
Not meet or fit; not proper; unbecoming; unsuitable; -- usuallyfollowed by for. "Unmeet for a wife." Tennyson.And all unmeet our carpet floors. Emerson.-- Un*meet"ly, adv.-- Un*meet"ness, n.
A meteorite characterized by the presence of but a small amountof metallic iron.
To purge of faults; to make better; to correct; esp., to makecorrections in (a literary work); to alter for the better by textualcriticism, generally verbal.
The operation of sewing up a laceration of the neck of theuterus.
The power or capacity of receiving impressions, as those of theexternal senses.
